  "doc_id": "32722",
  "text": "Here, we have built 44 models of Ca v 2.1 with MTSmodified engineered cysteines and used Monte Carlo (MC) minimizations (MCMs) to predict energetically possible orientations of MTS-modified side chains in the channels. We found that the residual current observed upon 2-(trimethylammonium)ethyl MTS (MTSET) application [CITATION_1] correlates with the predicted distance between the ammonium nitrogen in the MTS-modified cysteine and the pore axis, but does not correlate with the orientation of the C Pore-facing position * * ** ** ** Cytoplasm-facing position ** *** * * Data for Na v 1.4 are from [CITATION_2] . a Shown alignments of S5 [CITATION_3] and S6 [CITATION_4] ) segments were used to build the Ca v 2.1 models. b Bold-oblique and underlined characters indicate positions where MTSET inhibits channels with engineered cysteines ≥30 and <30%, respectively [CITATION_5] .",
